Accident Reporting (§ 107.9)

No later than 10 days after an operation (…) a remote pilot in command must report to the Federal Aviation Administration in a manner acceptable to the Administrator, any operation of the small unmanned aircraft involving at least:

    &lt;ul&gt;
    &lt;li class="small fragment"&gt;Serious injury to any person or any loss of consciousness; or&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li class="small fragment"&gt;Damage to any property, other than the small unmanned aircraft, unless the cost of repair (including materials and labor) or fair market value of the property does not exceed &lt;strong&gt;$500&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="right"&gt;
    &lt;img src="img/rules/drone-crash-test.png"&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;



